    "introduction": "DAHÉLI HALL [dah.hay.lee] is an LA-based performer and writer. Currently, she is a writer on Netflix's DEAR WHITE PEOPLE and plays the parody Oprah character “Dereca.\"  Dahéli is also a recurring character on Netflix's GRACE & FRANKIE and is known as a cast member and writer on S13 of Fox’s MADtv. Recently, Dahéli co-created a single-camera comedy for BET that Ed Helm's Pacific Electric Picture Company is producing. Dahéli studied at The Groundlings and UCB and received her BFA from NYU Tisch School and her MFA from the Stark Program at USC. Dahéli is a native of Miami, FL, and is of Jamaican and Haitian parentage.",
